title: Independent candidate Taj Muhammad wins PK-35 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Taj Muhammad has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-35 Battagram-II by securing 24,142 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was JUI-P candidate Wali Muhammad Khan who bagged 17,340 votes.
Votersâ€™ turnout remained 31.10 per cent.
